    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix crcTableInit() fails due to missing simde_mm_setr_epi32 definition\n\n### Summary\nThe `crcTableInit()` function in `crc_byte.c` fails to properly initialize CRC lookup tables because it calls `simde_mm_setr_epi32()` which is not defined anywhere in the codebase. This leads to compilation errors or runtime issues when trying to use CRC functionality.\n\nThe function is used during initialization in multiple places but fails silently or with errors due to the missing SIMD intrinsic.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/sse_intrin.h`: Added definitions for `simde_mm_setr_epi32()` and `simde_mm_set_epi32()` \n- These functions are now available for all modules that include `sse_intrin.h` directly or indirectly through `crc.h`\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Call `crcTableInit()` during program initialization\n2. Observe that the function fails to properly initialize the CRC tables\n3. Any subsequent CRC operations will produce incorrect results or segfault\n\nThe issue manifests as:\n- Incorrect CRC calculations in LTE/NR transport channels\n- Potential segfaults when accessing uninitialized CRC lookup tables\n- Silent data corruption in encoded/decoded transport blocks\n\nThis affects all modules that depend on CRC functionality including:\n- Transport block CRC calculation\n- PDSCH/PUSCH processing\n- RACH preamble detection\n- DCI CRC verification\n"
}